I don't
see anything.

511
00:55:35.600 --> 00:55:38.700
Be real still.

512
00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:44.100
Sometimes you
feel it inside.

513
00:55:44.200 --> 00:55:46.900
like you're falling down
real fast.

514
00:55:47.000 --> 00:55:49.800
but you're really
Just standing still.

515
00:55:54.200 --> 00:55:58.300
You ever feel the prickly things
on the back of your neck?

516
00:55:58.400 --> 00:56:01.200
Yes.

517
00:56:01.200 --> 00:56:05.000
And the tiny hairs on your arm.
you know. when they stand up?

518
00:56:05.000 --> 00:56:07.500
Yes.

519
00:56:09.100 --> 00:56:11.800
That's them.

520
00:56:14.300 --> 00:56:16.500
When they get mad.

521
00:56:20.100 --> 00:56:22.700
it gets cold.

522
00:56:38.600 --> 00:56:42.200
I don't see anything.
Are you sure they're there?

523
00:56:43.800 --> 00:56:46.100
Cole?

524
00:56:47.800 --> 00:56:50.500
Please make them leave.

525
00:56:50.500 --> 00:56:52.900
I'm workin' on it.

526
00:56:54.800 --> 00:56:57.100
Come on.

527
00:57:22.800 --> 00:57:25.500
Aah!

528
00:57:39.700 --> 00:57:43.000
Mommy. Daddy?

529
00:57:45.100 --> 00:57:47.500
My throat hurts.

530
00:57:55.600 --> 00:57:57.500
Run! Run!

531
00:57:58.900 --> 00:58:00.800
Pedia Ease
cough suppressant.

532
00:58:00.800 --> 00:58:04.900
- Gentle. fast. effect--
- Cole.

533
00:58:06.600 --> 00:58:08.900
I don't care what they say.
this thing is broken.

534
00:58:16.600 --> 00:58:18.800
Take 'em off.

535
00:58:22.300 --> 00:58:24.900
I don't want them
on my table.

536
00:58:29.200 --> 00:58:32.100
I saw what was in your bureau drawer
when I was cleaning.

537
00:58:32.200 --> 00:58:34.000
Got something
you want to confess?

538
00:58:37.000 --> 00:58:40.400
Hmm?
The bumblebee pendant?

539
00:58:40.500 --> 00:58:42.900
Why do you
keep taking it?

540
00:58:46.500 --> 00:58:48.600
It was Grandma's.

541
00:58:48.700 --> 00:58:51.800
You know. what if it broke?
You know how sad I'd be.

542
00:58:54.000 --> 00:58:56.600
You'd cry 'cause you
miss Grandma so much.

543
00:58:57.900 --> 00:59:00.200
That's right.

544
00:59:03.800 --> 00:59:07.200
Sometimes people think
they lose things.

545
00:59:09.100 --> 00:59:12.700
and they really didn't lose them--
it just gets moved.

546
00:59:12.800 --> 00:59:15.000
So. did you move
the bumblebee pendant?

547
00:59:23.100 --> 00:59:25.100
Don't get mad.

548
00:59:25.200 --> 00:59:27.100
So. who moved it
this time?

549
00:59:27.200 --> 00:59:30.700
Maybe someone came in our house.
took the bumblebee pendant
out of my closet...

550
00:59:30.800 --> 00:59:33.000
and placed it nicely
in your drawer.

551
00:59:34.200 --> 00:59:37.400
- Maybe.
- [Sighs] God. I am so tired. Cole.

552
00:59:37.400 --> 00:59:39.800
I'm tired in my body.
I'm tired in my mind.

553
00:59:39.900 --> 00:59:42.800
I'm... tired
in my heart.

554
00:59:42.900 --> 00:59:44.900
I need some help.

555
00:59:44.900 --> 00:59:49.000
You know. I don't know if you
noticed. but our little family
isn't doing so good.

556
00:59:49.100 --> 00:59:51.000
I mean.
I've been praying.

557
00:59:51.000 --> 00:59:54.000
but I must not
be praying right.

558
00:59:54.000 --> 00:59:56.800
Looks like we're just gonna have to
answer each other's prayers.

559
01:00:00.300 --> 01:00:03.000
If we can't talk to each other.
we're not gonna make it.

560
01:00:06.600 --> 01:00:10.100
Now. tell me. baby.
I- I- I won't get mad. honey.

561
01:00:10.200 --> 01:00:12.700
Did you take
the bumblebee pendant?

562
01:00:20.800 --> 01:00:23.200
- No.

563
01:00:24.800 --> 01:00:27.500
You've had enough roast beef.
You need to leave the table.

564
01:00:30.000 --> 01:00:32.100
Go!

565
01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:58.800
Hey. come on. I'll show you where
my dad keeps his gun. Come on.

566
01:01:03.800 --> 01:01:07.300
Sebastian. come on!

567
01:01:07.400 --> 01:01:11.200
- Mama?

568
01:01:15.500 --> 01:01:18.100
If you're not
very mad.

569
01:01:18.200 --> 01:01:20.600
can I sleep
in your bed tonight?

570
01:01:22.400 --> 01:01:24.900
Look at my face.

571
01:01:25.000 --> 01:01:27.700
I'm not very mad.

572
01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:34.200
- Baby. why are you shaking?

573
01:01:35.400 --> 01:01:37.500
Cole. what's wrong?

574
01:01:37.600 --> 01:01:41.200
Oh. God.
please tell me!

575
01:01:41.300 --> 01:01:44.500
Oh. please.

576
01:01:45.700 --> 01:01:48.200
Oh.

577
01:01:57.000 --> 01:01:59.800
It's Edwardian.
beautifully worked...

578
01:01:59.800 --> 01:02:04.700
with mine- cut diamonds
and an actual color Burmese sapphire.

579
01:02:04.800 --> 01:02:07.300
It's timeless.

580
01:02:07.400 --> 01:02:09.700
- Oh.

581
01:02:09.700 --> 01:02:12.100
You. uh...

582
01:02:12.200 --> 01:02:14.800
got anything
a little plainer?

583
01:02:14.800 --> 01:02:19.400
Plainer? You want a plain ring
to go with your plain fiance?
Is that how it is?

584
01:02:19.500 --> 01:02:23.200
No! Baby.
don't get in a tissy.

585
01:02:25.300 --> 01:02:29.800
Uh--
You're so beautiful.

586
01:02:29.900 --> 01:02:33.400
You're like a Burmese sapphire
all by yourself.

587
01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:36.200
- You don't need all that.
- Uh- huh.

588
01:02:36.300 --> 01:02:38.700
Why don't you
try it on...

589
01:02:38.800 --> 01:02:40.900
and see how you both
feel about it.

590
01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:49.400
There. How does
that feel?

591
01:02:49.400 --> 01:02:53.600
I think this piece.
um. communicates a longing.

592
01:02:53.600 --> 01:02:56.500
I imagine that the woman
who owned it...

593
01:02:56.600 --> 01:02:59.600
loved a man that she
couldn't be with.

594
01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:04.000
Did he have wavy hair
and chestnut eyes?

595
01:03:04.100 --> 01:03:08.000
- Huh?
- Um. I don't know. but...

596
01:03:08.100 --> 01:03:10.900
a lot of the pieces
in this store communicate.

597
01:03:11.000 --> 01:03:14.300
and I think you should choose
a piece that speaks to you.

598
01:03:15.700 --> 01:03:20.300
I think maybe when people own things
and then they pass away.

599
01:03:20.400 --> 01:03:23.700
a part of themselves gets
printed on those things.

600
01:03:23.800 --> 01:03:27.300
like...
like fingerprints.

601
01:03:29.300 --> 01:03:31.300
I'll just
wrap it up.

602
01:03:37.900 --> 01:03:40.100
You don't need a guy
with a Master's.

603
01:03:40.200 --> 01:03:42.800
You need a wrestler with a neck
larger than his head.

604
01:03:42.900 --> 01:03:46.000
No. I need a wrestler with a Master´s.

605
01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:49.500
- What's this?
- Happy birthday.

606
01:03:49.600 --> 01:03:51.800
- For me?
- Mm- hmm.

607
01:03:58.900 --> 01:04:03.000
It's a...
first edition.

608
01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:05.400
- Wow.

609
01:04:05.500 --> 01:04:08.200
- You know. this is too much.
- No.

610
01:04:08.300 --> 01:04:10.200
Took it out of
your Christmas bonus.

611
01:04:10.200 --> 01:04:14.300
It´s perfect. Anna.

612
01:04:14.400 --> 01:04:17.800
- Thanks.

613
01:04:22.100 --> 01:04:24.900
What do you want
more than anything?

614
01:04:24.900 --> 01:04:27.100
I don't know.

615
01:04:27.100 --> 01:04:29.800
- I've told you what I want.

616
01:04:32.400 --> 01:04:34.300
I know what I want.

617
01:04:36.400 --> 01:04:39.000
I want to be able to
talk to my wife again.

618
01:04:41.200 --> 01:04:44.400
The way we used to
talk to each other.

619
01:04:44.500 --> 01:04:47.000
Like there was no one else
in the world except us.

620
01:04:49.100 --> 01:04:51.000
How are you gonna do that?

621
01:04:56.300 --> 01:04:58.200
Can't be your doctor
anymore.

622
01:04:58.200 --> 01:05:02.600
I haven't paid enough
attention to my family.

623
01:05:02.700 --> 01:05:04.700
Bad things happen
when you do that.

624
01:05:06.400 --> 01:05:08.700
Do you understand?

625
01:05:08.800 --> 01:05:12.500
- I'm going to transfer you.
I know two psychologists.
- Don't fail me.

626
01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:17.400
Don't give up. You're the only one
who can help me. I know it.

627
01:05:19.100 --> 01:05:21.800
- I can't help you.
- [Sobbing]

628
01:05:22.900 --> 01:05:24.700
You--

629
01:05:24.800 --> 01:05:27.800
Someone else
can help you.

630
01:05:31.400 --> 01:05:34.300
You believe me. right?

631
01:05:37.500 --> 01:05:40.000
Dr. Crowe. you believe
my secret. right?

632
01:05:42.100 --> 01:05:44.800
I don't know how
to answer that. Cole.

633
01:05:54.600 --> 01:05:57.400
How can you help me...

634
01:05:57.500 --> 01:06:00.100
if you don't believe me?

635
01:06:03.600 --> 01:06:07.600
Some magic's real.

636
01:06:22.200 --> 01:06:26.000
Do you know why you're
afraid when you're alone?

637
01:06:26.200 --> 01:06:29.800
I do.
I do.

638
01:06:36.800 --> 01:06:40.700
I´m sorry. Vincent. I hope I
didn´t leave you alone too long.

639
01:06:40.800 --> 01:06:43.800
Whew.
It's cold in here.

640
01:06:46.400 --> 01:06:49.700
Vincent.
why are you crying?

641
01:06:53.600 --> 01:06:56.800
You won´t believe.

642
01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:05.900
Sorry. Vincent. I hope
I didn't leave you alone too long.

643
01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:09.000
Whew.
It's coldin here.

644
01:07:11.600 --> 01:07:14.500
- Vincent--

645
01:07:14.600 --> 01:07:18.700
Whew.
It's cold in here.

646
01:07:23.900 --> 01:07:27.300
- Nah. you know what?
I never liked him either.

647
01:07:27.400 --> 01:07:29.800
When I was a kid.
I had this blood test done.

648
01:07:29.800 --> 01:07:34.200
- and I threw up chili cheese
fries allover this male nurse.

649
01:07:35.400 --> 01:07:38.000
Excuse me.
Dr. Reed is on line two.

650
01:07:38.100 --> 01:07:40.700
Vincent. will you
excuse me? I have to take this.

651
01:07:40.800 --> 01:07:43.000
- Just give me a minute. okay?
- Okay.

652
01:08:55.100 --> 01:08:57.300
No entiendes.

653
01:08:57.300 --> 01:08:59.800
Yo no quiero morir.

654
01:09:06.700 --> 01:09:08.600
Yo no quiero morir.

655
01:09:08.600 --> 01:09:11.400
- Oh. my God.
- Yo no quiero morir!

656
01:09:17.100 --> 01:09:20.800
You been
running around?

657
01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.100
Make you
feel better?

658
01:09:26.400 --> 01:09:28.900
I like to run around.
It's good exercise.

659
01:09:32.700 --> 01:09:34.600
Do you want to ask me
questions now?

660
01:09:36.600 --> 01:09:40.100
Want to be a lance corporal in Company
"M" Third Battalion. Seventh Marines?

661
01:09:40.200 --> 01:09:43.100
We're being dispatched
into the Quang Nam province.

662
01:09:43.200 --> 01:09:45.500
Maybe later.

663
01:09:47.700 --> 01:09:49.600
Something happened.
didn't it?

664
01:09:52.700 --> 01:09:55.100
You wiggling out?

665
01:09:56.600 --> 01:09:59.500
Yes.
I think I am.

666
01:10:02.200 --> 01:10:05.300
Do you know what
"Yo no quiero morir" means?

667
01:10:05.400 --> 01:10:08.600
It's Spanish.
It means "I don't want to die. "

668
01:10:11.200 --> 01:10:13.700
What do you think these ghosts want
when they talk to you?

669
01:10:21.400 --> 01:10:23.500
I want you to
think about it. Cole.

670
01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:28.400
I want you to think about it
really carefully.

671
01:10:28.400 --> 01:10:31.000
What do you think
they want?

672
01:10:34.600 --> 01:10:38.800
- Just help.
- That's right. That's what I think too.

673
01:10:38.900 --> 01:10:41.200
They just want help.
even the scary ones.

674
01:10:41.300 --> 01:10:44.400
I think I might know a way
to make them go away.

675
01:10:44.400 --> 01:10:47.200
How?

676
01:10:47.300 --> 01:10:49.600
Listen to them.

677
01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:53.200
What if they
don't want help?

678
01:10:53.200 --> 01:10:56.500
What if they're just angry and they
Just want to hurt somebody?

679
01:10:56.600 --> 01:10:58.800
I don't think
that's the way it works.

680
01:10:58.900 --> 01:11:01.400
How do you know
for sure?

681
01:11:02.800 --> 01:11:05.400
I don't.

682
01:11:23.800 --> 01:11:26.900
- Hey!

683
01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:29.800
- Hey! Hey!

684
01:11:45.500 --> 01:11:49.500
What's happening?

685
01:11:49.600 --> 01:11:53.700
What´s happening?

686
01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:58.100
Go!

687
01:12:09.400 --> 01:12:12.100
What's happening
to you?

688
01:12:12.200 --> 01:12:15.200
Is someone hurting you?
I'll kick their ass.

689
01:12:15.300 --> 01:12:18.400
Cole. if they're
hurting you--

690
01:12:30.300 --> 01:12:33.200
Mama. you sleep now.

691
01:14:34.600 --> 01:14:37.300
I'm feeling
much better now.

692
01:14:41.600 --> 01:14:44.400
Do you want to
tell me something?

693
01:15:18.800 --> 01:15:21.600
She came a long way
to visit me. didn't she?

694
01:15:22.900 --> 01:15:25.600
I guess she did.

695
01:16:09.600 --> 01:16:11.700
Can you get
some water?

696
01:16:15.400 --> 01:16:17.200
That's her sister.

697
01:16:34.300 --> 01:16:38.500
You know. when I went through this
with my father's cancer--

698
01:16:38.600 --> 01:16:41.700
I just can't imagine a child
being in bed for two years.

699
01:16:41.800 --> 01:16:44.200
How many--
How many doctors?

700
01:16:44.300 --> 01:16:47.100
- I think it was six.
- Six different doctors?

701
01:16:47.200 --> 01:16:49.500
I think so. yes.

702
01:16:55.100 --> 01:16:59.400
I just heard the. uh.
little one is falling ill now.

703
01:16:59.400 --> 01:17:01.700
God help them.

704
01:17:20.400 --> 01:17:22.800
Don't go home.
okay?

705
01:17:22.800 --> 01:17:25.200
I definitely won't.

706
01:18:18.200 --> 01:18:20.700
Aah!
[Panting]

707
01:19:18.700 --> 01:19:21.000
Mister?

708
01:19:23.900 --> 01:19:26.200
Excuse me. mister.

709
01:19:30.300 --> 01:19:32.700
Are you
Kyra's daddy?

710
01:19:45.600 --> 01:19:49.100
It's for you.

711
01:19:49.100 --> 01:19:52.100
Sh- She wanted
to tell you something.

712
01:20:28.600 --> 01:20:31.000
Oh. no. here he comes.
He's coming my way. Psst!

713
01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:38.300
Would you like to dance?

714
01:20:38.300 --> 01:20:42.200
Well. actually.
I just came with my friends.

715
01:20:42.200 --> 01:20:44.600
Oh. well.
how about this?

716
01:20:44.700 --> 01:20:48.000
We can dance for a little bit.
and if you don't like the way I dance.

717
01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:49.900
you can kick me.

718
01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:52.000
Oh. okay then.

719
01:21:59.200 --> 01:22:02.200
It's time for lunch. Kyra.

720
01:22:06.200 --> 01:22:08.800
- I'm feeling much better now.
- That's so great. honey.

721
01:22:08.900 --> 01:22:11.100
It´s time for your food.

722
01:22:13.000 --> 01:22:15.200
Can I go outside
if I eat this?

723
01:22:15.200 --> 01:22:17.500
I don't know. You know how
you get sick in the afternoons.

724
01:22:17.600 --> 01:22:20.200
We'll see.

725
01:22:21.800 --> 01:22:25.500
Don't say that it tastes funny.
You know I don't like to hear that.

726
01:22:28.100 --> 01:22:32.200
Tami's mom called.

727
01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:49.300
You were
keeping her sick.

728
01:23:05.400 --> 01:23:08.000
You liked it.
she said.

729
01:23:10.900 --> 01:23:13.900
She looked out
for you.

730
01:23:14.000 --> 01:23:16.200
Is Kyra coming back?

731
01:23:19.200 --> 01:23:22.000
Not anymore.

732
01:23:28.700 --> 01:23:30.900
I think that's enough.
That's enough makeup.

733
01:23:30.900 --> 01:23:33.400
Okay.

734
01:23:33.500 --> 01:23:37.000
- They're calling for the stable boy.
- We have to hurry!

735
01:23:40.400 --> 01:23:42.600
Who. uh--
Who were you talking to?

736
01:23:49.200 --> 01:23:52.100
Just practicing
my lines.

737
01:23:55.100 --> 01:23:57.800
Thanks for giving me this part.
Mr. Cunningham.

738
01:23:57.900 --> 01:24:01.500
You know. when I went to school
here. there was a terrible fire
in this section of the theater.

739
01:24:01.600 --> 01:24:03.500
They rebuilt
the whole thing.

740
01:24:03.600 --> 01:24:06.400
Yeah. I know.

741
01:24:16.100 --> 01:24:20.800
Only he who is pure of heart
can take the sword from the stone.

742
01:24:20.900 --> 01:24:23.400
Let the boy try.

743
01:24:30.300 --> 01:24:33.200
He is a stable boy.
He cleans up after the horses.

744
01:24:33.300 --> 01:24:35.900
- Silence. village idiot.

745
01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:38.700
Let the boy
step forward.

746
01:25:05.000 --> 01:25:07.700
Hail. King Arthur!

747
01:25:12.200 --> 01:25:14.100
Yea!

748
01:25:38.400 --> 01:25:41.300
I thought you were
really great in the play. Cole.

749
01:25:41.300 --> 01:25:43.400
- Really?
- Yeah.

750
01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:45.800
- You know what else?
- What?

751
01:25:45.900 --> 01:25:50.100
I thought Tommy Tammisimo
sucked big time.

752
01:25:57.000 --> 01:26:00.300
I got an idea how you can talk
to your wife.

753
01:26:00.300 --> 01:26:03.500
Wait till
she's asleep.

754
01:26:03.500 --> 01:26:06.900
Then she'll listen to you
and she won't even know it.

755
01:26:14.000 --> 01:26:17.000
I'm not gonna see you
anymore. am I?

756
01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:21.800
I think we said everything
we needed to say.

757
01:26:23.200 --> 01:26:26.100
Maybe it's time to say things
to someone closer to you.

758
01:26:28.000 --> 01:26:31.000
Maybe we can pretend like we're
gonna see each other tomorrow.

759
01:26:33.200 --> 01:26:35.500
Just for pretend.

760
01:26:41.500 --> 01:26:43.800
Okay.

761
01:26:47.800 --> 01:26:50.200
I'm gonna go now.

762
01:26:56.000 --> 01:26:58.200
I'll see you
tomorrow. Cole.

763
01:27:24.300 --> 01:27:27.700
I'm okay. Officer.
I- I'm okay.

764
01:27:27.800 --> 01:27:30.000
I don't know
what happened.

765
01:27:35.100 --> 01:27:37.900
Hmm.

766
01:27:38.000 --> 01:27:41.000
Geez. I hope
nobody got hurt.

767
01:27:44.000 --> 01:27:47.000
You're very quiet.

768
01:27:47.100 --> 01:27:50.300
You're mad I missed
the play. aren't you?

769
01:27:50.400 --> 01:27:52.600
I have two jobs. baby.

770
01:27:52.700 --> 01:27:55.600
You know how important
they are for us.

771
01:27:57.500 --> 01:27:59.900
I'd give anything
to have been there.

772
01:28:11.300 --> 01:28:13.500
I'm ready to communicate
with you now.

773
01:28:18.500 --> 01:28:20.500
Communicate?

774
01:28:22.000 --> 01:28:24.200
Tell you my secrets.

775
01:28:25.800 --> 01:28:28.100
What is it?

776
01:28:31.700 --> 01:28:34.400
You know the accident
up there?

777
01:28:34.500 --> 01:28:37.400
Yeah.

778
01:28:37.400 --> 01:28:39.400
Someone got hurt.

779
01:28:39.500 --> 01:28:41.600
They did?

780
01:28:41.700 --> 01:28:45.100
A lady.

781
01:28:45.200 --> 01:28:47.400
She died.

782
01:28:47.400 --> 01:28:49.800
Oh. my God.
What. you can see her?

783
01:28:51.200 --> 01:28:54.100
- Yes.
- Where is she?

784
01:28:57.500 --> 01:29:01.300
Standing next to
my window.

785
01:29:07.100 --> 01:29:10.000
Cole. you're
scaring me.

786
01:29:10.000 --> 01:29:12.200
They scare me too
sometimes.

787
01:29:14.800 --> 01:29:17.000
They?

788
01:29:19.700 --> 01:29:21.600
Ghosts.

789
01:29:25.800 --> 01:29:28.100
You see ghosts. Cole?

790
01:29:30.200 --> 01:29:33.000
They want me to
do things for them.

791
01:29:35.600 --> 01:29:37.700
They--
They talk to you?

792
01:29:37.800 --> 01:29:40.800
They tell you
to do things?

793
01:29:41.800 --> 01:29:44.600
They're the ones
that used to hurt me.

794
01:29:46.000 --> 01:29:48.700
What are you
thinking. Mama?

795
01:29:48.800 --> 01:29:53.200
- You think I'm a freak?
- Look at my face.

796
01:29:53.300 --> 01:29:56.100
I would never think that
about you. Ever.

797
01:29:57.400 --> 01:29:59.700
- Got it?
- Got it.

798
01:30:06.800 --> 01:30:08.700
Just let me think
for a minute.

799
01:30:12.400 --> 01:30:14.400
Grandma says hi.

800
01:30:17.800 --> 01:30:20.800
She says she's sorry for
taking the bumblebee pendant.

801
01:30:20.900 --> 01:30:23.400
She just
likes it a lot.

802
01:30:25.800 --> 01:30:29.500
- What?
- Grandma comes to visit me sometimes.

803
01:30:31.800 --> 01:30:34.500
Cole. that's
very wrong.

804
01:30:34.600 --> 01:30:37.000
- Grandma's gone. you know that.
- I know.

805
01:30:37.100 --> 01:30:40.300
- She wanted me to tell you--
- Cole. please stop.

806
01:30:40.300 --> 01:30:43.000
She wanted me to tell you
she saw you dance.

807
01:30:44.600 --> 01:30:48.000
She said
when you were little.

808
01:30:48.100 --> 01:30:50.000
you and her
had a fight...

809
01:30:50.000 --> 01:30:52.700
right before
your dance recital.

810
01:30:54.800 --> 01:30:59.400
- You thought she didn´t come
to see your dance.

811
01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:05.300
She did.

812
01:31:10.400 --> 01:31:14.100
She hid in the back
so you wouldn't see.

813
01:31:14.200 --> 01:31:16.900
Sh- She said you were
like an angel.

814
01:31:21.300 --> 01:31:23.400
- She said...

815
01:31:23.400 --> 01:31:26.800
you came to the place
where they buried her.

816
01:31:28.900 --> 01:31:31.200
asked her a question.

817
01:31:33.700 --> 01:31:37.800
She said
the answer is...

818
01:31:37.900 --> 01:31:39.800
every day.

819
01:31:42.200 --> 01:31:44.600
What did you ask?

820
01:31:52.300 --> 01:31:55.400
Do--

821
01:31:55.400 --> 01:31:59.000
Do I make her proud?

822
01:32:01.400 --> 01:32:03.700
Mama.

823
01:32:31.900 --> 01:32:34.300
Hi. everybody.
As most of you know.

824
01:32:34.400 --> 01:32:36.900
I'm not
used to doing this.

825
01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:40.500
and I promised Anna
that I'd try not to embarrass her.

826
01:32:40.600 --> 01:32:44.500
I'll leave that to her mother.

827
01:32:44.600 --> 01:32:46.700
But we do want to thank
all of you for coming...

828
01:32:46.800 --> 01:32:49.500
and for sharing
this wonderful day with us.

829
01:32:49.600 --> 01:32:52.300
It's bitter sweet almost.
for me.

830
01:32:52.400 --> 01:32:54.500
'cause I hate
giving her up.

831
01:32:54.600 --> 01:32:56.600
Anna?

832
01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:07.900
I miss you.

833
01:33:13.600 --> 01:33:16.000
I miss you too.

834
01:33:16.100 --> 01:33:18.800
Why. Malcolm?

835
01:33:18.900 --> 01:33:21.500
What?

836
01:33:23.200 --> 01:33:26.700
- What is it?
- Why did you leave me?

837
01:33:26.800 --> 01:33:30.000
I didn't leave you.

838
01:33:49.700 --> 01:33:53.400
I see people.

839
01:33:53.400 --> 01:33:55.800
They don't know
they're dead.

840
01:33:59.800 --> 01:34:04.400
- How often
do you see them?
- All the time.

841
01:34:06.900 --> 01:34:08.800
They're everywhere.

842
01:34:19.600 --> 01:34:22.000
They only see
what they want to see.

843
01:34:27.200 --> 01:34:30.600
Okay. Mikey.

844
01:34:30.600 --> 01:34:33.800
Come on.
Give me a minute.

845
01:35:10.300 --> 01:35:12.500
- Oh. God.

846
01:35:12.600 --> 01:35:16.100
- It doesn't even hurt.
- Let me see.

847
01:35:18.600 --> 01:35:21.700
- Let me see. Put your hand--

848
01:35:21.700 --> 01:35:23.900
Oh. God.

849
01:35:29.000 --> 01:35:31.000
- Okay.

850
01:35:49.200 --> 01:35:52.900
I think I'm okay.
Really. I think it just went--

851
01:35:53.000 --> 01:35:55.200
went in and out.

852
01:35:58.100 --> 01:36:01.200
It doesn't even
hurt anymore.

853
01:36:29.300 --> 01:36:31.700
I think
I can go now.

854
01:36:35.300 --> 01:36:37.600
I just needed
to do a couple things.

855
01:36:42.500 --> 01:36:45.100
I needed
to help someone.

856
01:36:47.500 --> 01:36:49.700
I think I did.

857
01:36:55.500 --> 01:36:58.100
And I needed
to tell you something.

858
01:37:02.700 --> 01:37:05.700
You were never second.

859
01:37:05.800 --> 01:37:08.200
Ever.

860
01:37:10.400 --> 01:37:13.000
I love you.

861
01:37:18.300 --> 01:37:20.400
You sleep now.

862
01:37:22.200 --> 01:37:24.700
Everything will be
different in the morning.

863
01:37:30.600 --> 01:37:33.400
Good night.
Malcolm.

864
01:37:38.100 --> 01:37:40.400
Good night.
sweetheart.
